OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FKen Bruce says early Radio 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25F2 exit 'seems a shame'     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, DJ Ken Bruce has said it "seems a      
OL,6, shame" to be leaving his Radio 2 show  
OL,7, earlier than anticipated, after the BBC
OL,8, asked him not to complete his contract.
OL,10,FThe Scottish presenter, 72, is leaving 
OL,11,Fthe station to host a new show on      
OL,12,Fcommercial station Greatest Hits Radio.
OL,14,FHe told Radio 4's Today programme:     
OL,15,F"It's entirely within the BBC's right  
OL,16,Fto ask me to step away a little early. 
OL,18,F"But for the sake of 17 days, which was
OL,19,Fall that was remaining (on my          
OL,20,Fcontract), it seems a shame."          
